-- Former Credit Suisse Banker Barret Creates M&A Boutique
-- B y   F r a n c o i s   d e   B e a u p u y
-- 2012-10-15T11:29:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-15/former-credit-suisse-banker-barret-creates-m-a-boutique.html
Olivier Barret, Pierre-Arnaud de
Lacharriere and Francois Vigne are joining forces to create
Sycomore Corporate Finance, an acquisition and financial
advisory boutique.  The three partners own a majority stake in the Paris-based
firm backed by Sycomore Asset Management, according to a
statement by the new firm. Sycomore Corporate Finance has a team
of about 10 investment bankers and a network of partners abroad.  Barret was co-head of  Credit Suisse (CSGN)  AG’s investment bank in
France, Belgium and Luxembourg since 2009, after spending more
than 15 years at  Morgan Stanley. (MS)   In 2001, Lacharriere took part in the takeover of Hawkpoint
Partners Ltd., NatWest Group’s investment bank, as well as the
creation and development of its Paris office. Before that, he
worked almost 10 years at Clinvest, Credit Lyonnais’s investment
bank.  Vigne started his carrier at CCF Charterhouse Ltd. in 1995
before joining the mergers and acquisitions department of  Credit
Agricole SA. (ACA)  He was managing director at  Societe Generale SA (GLE) ’s
corporate finance unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francois de Beaupuy in Paris at 
